==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Benefit society
<hw>Benefit society</hw>. <def>A society or association formed for
mutual insurance, as among tradesmen or in labor unions, to provide for
relief in sickness, old age, and for the expenses of burial. Usually
called <altname>friendly society</altname> in Great Britain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Beneme</ent>⟦br⟧
